This paper is about distributed deep learning optimization, which is a topic that falls under several sub-categories in computer science. The most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper proposes a new optimization method for deep neural networks. The second likely sub-category is cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), as the paper focuses on distributed optimization on a cluster of workers. The third likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), as the paper conducts experiments on CNN models commonly used in computer vision tasks. The fourth likely sub-category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), as the paper proposes a new method for optimizing neural networks. The fifth likely sub-category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), as the paper proposes a new algorithm for optimizing deep neural networks.
